    <text>
    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi> | (<hi rend="print">Railway Station | Orpington. S.E.R.</hi>)</placeName>
                    <date>Jan 2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> 1881.</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
                    <p>I thank you for the Photograph &amp; your kind new year wishes, which I very heartily return.<ref target="#foot.f2"/> I hope that your <hi rend="italic">[illeg]</hi> affairs prosper, &amp; I am well assured that you deserve that they sh<hi rend="superscript">d</hi>. prosper.— As for myself I am fairly well, but feel very old with failing strength.</p>
<p>My dear Sir | Yours sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">0.1 (<hi rend="italic">Railway … S.E.R.</hi>)] <hi rend="italic">parentheses added blue ink</hi> </note>
            </div>
            
            
        </div>
        
        
        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD misdated the letter; the year is established by the postmark.</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">Kovalevsky had sent a photograph of <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_7180.xml">Aleksey Ivanovich Butakoff</ref>; it has not been found (see <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 29, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-13588.xml">letter from V. O. Kovalevsky, 30 December 1881</ref>).</note>
            
            
        </div>
    
